    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Night Bush Presented Himself to America</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Donald Feldman letter says Dick Cheney, in his acceptance speech at Republican National Convention (Aug 3 article), spoke of the last eight years as a disaster for America, which they were not</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Dick Cheney, in his acceptance speech at the Republican National Convention, assured America that four years of a Gore administration would be a continuation of the eight years of the Clinton administration (front page, Aug. 3).</p>
        <p>I assume that he meant four more years of low inflation, a booming stock market, decreasing crime rates, fewer teenage pregnancies and decreasing abortion rates.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Dick Cheney, in his acceptance speech at the Republican National Convention, assured America that four years of a Gore administration would be a continuation of the eight years of the Clinton administration (front page, Aug. 3).</p>
        <p>I assume that he meant four more years of low inflation, a booming stock market, decreasing crime rates, fewer teenage pregnancies and decreasing abortion rates.</p>
        <p>This sounds pretty good to me, although I am somewhat surprised to hear a Republican admit it.</p>
        <p>DONALD FELDMAN  Los Alamos, N.M., Aug. 3, 2000</p>
      </block>
